title: NSCL/P sample 1
source_name_ch1: dental pulp stem cells extracted from deciduos tooth
treatment_protocol_ch1: No specific treatment was used in cells cultures. Growing cells were used in the media described above.
growth_protocol_ch1: Cells were cultured in DMEM-F12 (Life Technologies) supplemented with 15% Foetal Bovine Serum (HyClone), 1% Non-essential aminoacids solution (Life Technologies), 1% penicillin-streptomycin solution (Life Technologies), in a humidified incubator at 37oC and 5% CO2. For storage, cells were frozen in medium containing 90% FBS and 10% DMSO (LGC Biotecnologia). Protocols are also described in Bueno et al, 2011 Stem Cell Reviews and Reports.
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA isolation was performed with NucleoSpin RNA II kit (Macherey-Nagel), following manufacturer’s recommendations. RNA quality and concentration were assessed using Nanodrop 1000 and agarose gel electrophoresis. Only RNA samples with absorbance ratio 260/280 > 1.8, preserved rRNA ratio (28S/18S) and no signs of degradation were used.
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 6 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, 10 ug of cRNA were hybridized for 16 hr at 45C on GeneChip®Human Gene 1.0 ST Array. GeneChips were washed and stained in the Affymetrix Fluidics Station 450 and hybridized for 16 hr in the Affymetrix Hybridization Oven 640.
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G
description: gene expression data from dental pulp stem cells extracted from deciduos tooth
data_processing: Data were analyzed with Expression Console (Affymetrix) and normalized by RMA method.
